FBIS4-41622 "drsov123_f_94007" FBIS-SOV-94-123 Daily Report 26 Jun 1994 National Affairs Kuchma To Take Economic Measures First If Elected Kuchma To Take Economic Measures First If Elected LD2606140094 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1235 GMT 26 Jun 94 LD2606140094 Kiev UNIAN Ukrainian BFN [Text] Kiev -- To the question from a UNIAN correspondent: "What will you do if you find out that you have been elected president of Ukraine or that you have gone through to the second round of the election," Leonid Kuchma, a candidate for president of Ukraine, noted: "If I am not elected, I would cross myself with happiness." In the event of his election he would take his first steps in the economy because "the point from which one should begin is to bring order to one's home." With regard to possible cooperation with Vitaliy Masol, prime minister of Ukraine, if he is elected president, Leonid Kuchma replied that this is a question to which he does not yet know the answer at the moment.
